'I know BVB are still a great team,' said Lewandowski after the game. 'They're struggling at the moment.

'But I expect them to come catch up again and I know they will play in the Champions League again next season.'

Lewandowski's goal, which cancelled out Marco Reus' first-half header, was his first against Dortmund since joining German champions Bayern this summer.

