And while the striker pointed to the sky after finding the net he insisted it was not a celebration against his former employers. 

'It was not an easy game - for me, either,' he said. 'I did not celebrate  but it was an important goal and it was a goal for my dad.

'We were not perfect during the first half but the only important thing is that we got the three points.'

